I remember one day I was taking a bus from London to Oxford and ̱Let Down̨ started when the bus started rolling. While I had loved that song since OK Computer, the album it appeared on, was released, but on this particular day it seemed different.As the bus left the station and we passed the nearby train station, wove through the streets of London, and entered the motorway, the lyrics paralleled our journey.Transport, motorways and tramlinesStarting and then stoppingTaking off and landingThe emptiest of feelingsDisappointed people, clinging on to bottlesWhen it comes it's so, so, disappointingIt was a perfect song for a perfect ride.
